hypothesis: At least 2-3 PHILOSOPHY.md claims lack supporting evidence or contradict git history. P-164 (confirmation rate >80% = underchallenging) predicts we'll find falsifiable gaps in unchallenged claims.
method: Systematic audit of all 21 PHIL claims. Focused counter-evidence search on the 10 never-challenged claims (PHIL-2,6,7,10,12,14,17,18,19,20). For each: searched git log, experiments, lessons, and quantitative tools for contradicting evidence.

challenges_filed.counter_evidence: Truthful sub-score 1/3 (33% evidence_rate). Failing own defined metric (50% threshold). Binding constraint on F-EVAL1.
challenges_filed.required_action: Process one QUEUED challenge with measured falsification evidence

challenges_filed.counter_evidence: Zero peer-to-peer mutual swarming instances in 349 sessions. Mechanisms taxonomy says 'potential, not yet actual'. All interactions are parent→child.
challenges_filed.required_action: Run two swarm instances on separate repos, mutual orient→act→compress for ≥3 sessions

challenges_filed.counter_evidence: 5 documented breakage events (L-234, L-233, L-279, L-370). 729-file deletion most severe. All recovered. Advisory guards, not enforced.
challenges_filed.required_action: Refine wording to 'grow with resilient recovery' or add 'breaking is signal' qualifier

secondary_findings.note: 66% zero-citation rate on lessons. Compounding mechanism exists but integration efficiency is low. Modern agent architectures (MemGPT, Reflexion) partially close the gap.
Proxy-K drift 8.5%, total size 2.29x higher than period start. Compaction lags behind growth. Already partially addressed by PHIL-8 challenge (rising sawtooth).

meta_observation: P-164 prediction confirmed: confirmation rate remains 100% (0 DROPPED in 31 challenges). The challenge mechanism refines and confirms — it does not falsify. This is the same structural gap as PHIL-14 truthful failing: the swarm is better at adjusting than rejecting.
verdict: PARTIAL — 3 challenges filed, challenge rate improved 52.4%→66.7%. Zero-DROPPED pattern persists. The audit itself demonstrates the confirmation bias: even the counter-evidence found leads to REFINED, not DROPPED.
